Youtube and European regulations Digging more into this, I find out that Youtube posted a blog on September 22, 2020, annoucing the new changes to their policy. In this blog post, titled Using technology to more consistently apply age restrictions, Youtube team goes over the forthcoming European Union&amp;rsquo;s Audiovisual Media Services Directive, and how, under this directive, they have to make sure their user is over 18 to access restricted content.</description></item><item><title>Systems design explains the world: volume 1 - apenwarr</title><link>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/1twk2rtdkf/</link><pubDate>Mon, 08 Feb 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/1twk2rtdkf/</guid><description/></item><item><title>supercookie • welcome</title><link>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/7k8ijdwj+x/</link><pubDate>Sun, 07 Feb 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/7k8ijdwj+x/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Damned if you do, damned if you don’t: Censorship, Decentralized Networks and Moderation | Hacker Noon</title><link>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/tfqada32nc/</link><pubDate>Sat, 06 Feb 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/links/tfqada32nc/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Into the world of digital identities</title><link>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/posts/digital-identities-primer/</link><pubDate>Mon, 19 Oct 2020 21:25:40 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://thibmeu.github.io/ghpages/posts/digital-identities-primer/</guid><description>Into the world of digital identities The move to work from home (and not work remote) came with a lot of challenge. A growing pain for me has been the lack of a printer for administrative red tapes which is still a very paper based process.
